licate things with resource loss. A dedicated method could help cover line146 instead.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reassessing C3P0Registry Testing**\\n\\nIt looks like I can't directly cover the active call site in C3P0Registry.<clinit> on line 146, especially if the global resource is not working. I seem to need to remove that resource. I want to have a clear one-to-one mapping, possibly setting up a dedicated C3P0RegistryTest. I'm wondering if there's a better way to include helpers without making a separate dynamic-access class mapping. I need to think through how to structure my tests effectively without complicating things further.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_BsEUNiuCVacUrA9pO4l0zsuG|fc_0a8b8711862d4de20169fc0fb98c8881918b13772acd7bc32a", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.mchange/c3p0/0.9.5.4/user-code-filter.json", "limit": 100}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 454, "output": 1448, "cacheRead": 61952, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 63854, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778126756087, "responseId": "resp_0a8b8711862d4de20169fc0fa4aa4481919e4c883da407ba80"}}
